SIMPLE: bilateral
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bilateral
<hw>Bi*lat"er*al</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>bi-</ets> + <ets>lateral</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>bilat⟦eacute⟧ral</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having two sides;
arranged upon two sides; affecting two sides or two parties.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to the two sides
of a central area or organ, or of a central axis; <as>as,
<ex>bilateral</ex> symmetry in animals, where there is a similarity of
parts on the right and left sides of the body</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bilaterality</ent>⟦br⟧
